    <h2>About UIA</h2>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>The <a title="Union of International Associations" class="ext" href="../../../www.uia.org/default.htm" target="_blank">Union of International Associations<span class="ext"><span class="element-invisible"> (link is external)</span></span></a> (UIA) is a research institute and documentation centre, based in Brussels. It&nbsp;was&nbsp;<a class="ext" href="../../../uia.org/history" target="_blank">established<span class="ext"><span class="element-invisible"> (link is external)</span></span></a>&nbsp;in 1907, by&nbsp;<a class="ext" href="../../../www.uia.org/henri-la-fontaine-1854-1943" target="_blank">Henri la Fontaine<span class="ext"><span class="element-invisible"> (link is external)</span></span></a>&nbsp;(Nobel Peace Prize laureate of 1913), and&nbsp;<a href="../Paul%20Otlet">Paul Otlet</a>, a founding father of what is now&nbsp;called information science.<br>&nbsp;</p><p>Non-profit, apolitical, independent, and non-governmental in nature, the UIA has been a pioneer in the research, monitoring and provision of information on international&nbsp;organizations, international associations and their global challenges since 1907.</p><p><a title="Union of International Associations" class="ext" href="../../../www.uia.org/default.htm" target="_blank">www.uia.org<span class="ext"><span class="element-invisible"> (link is external)</span></span></a></p>  </div>
